#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 46"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "46. Cārittasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on visiting"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.98"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.362"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa932"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ "
"āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ bhattena nimantesi."
msgstr ""
"At that time a family that was supporting Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had "
"invited him to a meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Aññepi bhikkhū bhattena nimantesi."
msgstr "and they had invited other monks too."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ, kulāni "
"payirupāsati."
msgstr "But since Upananda was visiting other families before that meal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "the other monks said to that family,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "“dethāvuso, bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Please, give the meal.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please wait, Venerables, until Venerable Upananda arrives.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū … pe …"
msgstr "A second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "A third time those monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“dethāvuso, bhattaṃ; pure kālo atikkamatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please give the meal before the time for eating comes to an end.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Yampi mayaṃ, bhante, bhattaṃ karimhā ayyassa upanandassa kāraṇā."
msgstr "“But, Venerables, we made the meal because of Venerable Upananda."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "Please wait until he arrives.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa933"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā "
"āgacchati."
msgstr "Then, after visiting those families, Upananda arrived late,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Bhikkhū na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjiṃsu."
msgstr "and those monks did not eat as much as they had intended."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto nimantito sabhatto samāno "
"purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Upananda visit families first when invited to a meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu "
"cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.363"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you visit families first when invited to a meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa934"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ "
"āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa935"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.99"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa936"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ "
"saṃghassatthāya khādanīyaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards a family that was supporting Upananda sent non-staple food "
"to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "“ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṃghassa dātabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"They gave instructions that the food should be shown to Upananda and then "
"given to the Order."

#. </p><p>
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho "
"hoti."
msgstr "Just then Upananda had entered the village for alms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhū pucchiṃsu—"
msgstr "When those people arrived at the monastery,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo upanando”ti?"
msgstr "they asked for Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "“Esāvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho”ti."
msgstr "and they were told where he was."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.6"
msgid ""
"“Idaṃ, bhante, khādanīyaṃ ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṃghassa dātabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"They said, “Venerables, after showing it to Venerable Upananda, this non-"
"staple food is to be given to the Order.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "who then gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"“tena hi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahetvā nikkhipatha yāva upanando āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, monks, receive it and put it aside until Upananda returns.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa937"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.364"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ purebhattaṃ "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjitun”ti pacchābhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā "
"paṭikkami, khādanīyaṃ ussāriyittha."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Master had prohibited visiting families before the meal, "
"Upananda visited them after the meal instead. As a consequence he returned "
"late to the monastery, and the food had to be returned to the donors."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ "
"āpajjissatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda visit families after the meal?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.17"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you visit families after the meal?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa938"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.20"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or "
"afterwards, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa939"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa940"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvaradānasamaye kukkuccāyantā kulāni na "
"payirupāsanti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards it was the robe-giving season. But being afraid of "
"wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.2"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "As a result they only obtained a small amount of robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to visit families during the robe-giving season."

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Third preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
#. <span class="rule"><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa941"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.6"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or "
"afterwards, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reason is this:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa942"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs3.9"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa943"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.365"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvarakammaṃ karonti, attho ca hoti sūciyāpi "
"suttenapi satthakenapi."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards the monks were making a robe, and they needed a needle, "
"thread, and scissors."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti."
msgstr "But being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to visit families if you are making a robe."

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fourth preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.100"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa944"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.6"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or "
"afterwards, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. </span></p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa945"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs4.9"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Fifth sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa946"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti, attho ca hoti bhesajjehi."
msgstr "Soon afterwards there were sick monks who needed medicines."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.2"
msgid "Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti."
msgstr "But being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master. …"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.4"
msgid "anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā kulāni payirupāsituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to visit families after informing an available monk."

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa947"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.6"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā "
"purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or "
"afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.7"
msgid "Tatthāyaṃ samayo."
msgstr "The appropriate reasons are these:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.8"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr "it is the robe-giving season, he is making a robe.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs5.9"
msgid "(<em>46</em>:<strong>95</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.46.6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.6.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa948"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.366"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa949"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.6"
msgid "Nimantito nāma"
msgstr "Invited:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.7"
msgid "pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito."
msgstr "invited to eat any of the five staple foods."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa950"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.8"
msgid "Sabhatto nāma"
msgstr "To a meal:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.9"
msgid "yena nimantito tena sabhatto."
msgstr "the invitation includes a meal."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa951"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.10"
msgid "Santaṃ nāma"
msgstr "An available monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.11"
msgid "bhikkhuṃ sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ."
msgstr "he is able to inform and then enter."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa952"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.12"
msgid "Asantaṃ nāma"
msgstr "No available monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.13"
msgid "bhikkhuṃ na sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ."
msgstr "he is not able to inform and then enter."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa953"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.14"
msgid "Purebhattaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Beforehand:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.15"
msgid "yena nimantito taṃ abhuttāvī."
msgstr "he has not yet eaten what he has been invited to eat."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa954"></a>
#. VAR: kusaggenapi → aruṇuggamanepi (bj)
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.16"
msgid "Pacchābhattaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Afterwards:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.17"
msgid "yena nimantito taṃ antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"even if he has just eaten what fits on the tip of a blade of grass from what "
"he has been invited to eat."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa955"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.18"
msgid "Kulaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A family:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.19"
msgid "cattāri kulāni—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of families:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.20"
msgid "khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ."
msgstr ""
"aristocratic families, brahmin families, merchant families, worker families."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa956"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.21"
msgid "Kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Visits families:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.22"
msgid "aññassa gharūpacāraṃ okkamantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"if he enters the vicinity of someone else’s house, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.23"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he crosses the threshold with the first foot, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.24"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he crosses the threshold with the second foot, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa957"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.25"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.26"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa958"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.27"
msgid "Cīvaradānasamayo nāma"
msgstr "It is the robe-giving season:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. That is, the last month of the rainy season plus the four months of the cold season.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.28"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā."
msgstr ""
"for one who has not done the robe-making ceremony, it is the last month of "
"the rainy season. For one who has done the robe-making ceremony, it is the "
"five-month period."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa959"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.29"
msgid "Cīvarakārasamayo nāma"
msgstr "He is making a robe:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.1.30"
msgid "cīvare kayiramāne."
msgstr "when he is making a robe."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.6.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa960"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.1"
msgid ""
"Nimantite nimantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā "
"pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has been invited, and he perceives that he has, and he visits families "
"beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there "
"is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.2"
msgid ""
"Nimantite vematiko santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā "
"kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has been invited, but he is unsure if he has, and he visits families "
"beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, unless there "
"is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.367"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.3"
msgid ""
"Nimantite animantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā "
"pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has been invited, but he does not perceives that he has, and he visits "
"families beforehand or afterwards without informing an available monk, "
"unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.101"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa961"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.4"
msgid "Animantite nimantitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has not been invited, but he perceives that he has, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.5"
msgid "Animantite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he has not been invited,  but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.2.6"
msgid "Animantite animantitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he has not been invited, and he does not perceive that he has, there is "
"no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.46.6.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa962"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.3"
msgid "santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā pavisati,"
msgstr "if he enters after informing an available monk;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.4"
msgid "asantaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā pavisati,"
msgstr "if, when there is no available monk, he enters without informing;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.5"
msgid "aññassa gharena maggo hoti,"
msgstr "if the road passes someone else’s house;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.6"
msgid "gharūpacārena maggo hoti,"
msgstr "if the road passes the vicinity of someone else’s house;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.7"
msgid "antarārāmaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going between monasteries;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.8"
msgid "bhikkhunupassayaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to the dwelling place of nuns;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.9"
msgid "titthiyaseyyaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to the dwelling place of the ascetics of another sect;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.10"
msgid "paṭikkamanaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is returning to the monastery;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.11"
msgid "bhattiyagharaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he is going to a house for a meal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.12"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.13"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.14"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa963"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc46:pts-cs6.3.15"
msgid "Cārittasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on visiting, is finished."

